---

A hush falls as twilight descends,
a soft embrace to the day’s end,
while shadows stretch and sigh
beneath the weight of night’s shroud.
Stars blink awake, scattered wishes,
each twinkle a promise,
and in this tender silence,
I find solace in the air, a quiet peace.

- C Dale Young
